## System Components Summary

| Layer | Component | Technology | Responsibility |
|-------|-----------|------------|----------------|
| **Client** | Web Dashboard | React SPA | CA/MSME user interface |
| **Client** | WhatsApp/Email | SendGrid + Interakt | Alert receipt channels |
| **API** | Auth Service | FastAPI + JWT | Authentication & RBAC (4 roles) |
| **API** | REST API | FastAPI | 7 route groups, CRUD operations |
| **Processing** | APScheduler | Python AsyncIO | Time-based scraper triggering |
| **Processing** | Celery Workers | Celery 5.x | Async task execution (4 task types) |
| **Service** | Scraper Registry | curl_cffi + tenacity | 20+ government website scrapers |
| **Service** | LLM Processor | Gemini/OpenAI/Anthropic | Regulatory text extraction + alert generation |
| **Service** | Applicability Engine | Pure Python | JSONB rule matching against business profiles |
| **Service** | Alert Generator | Python + LLM | Personalised alert creation per business |
| **Service** | Delivery Service | SendGrid + httpx | Multi-channel alert dispatch |
| **Data** | PostgreSQL 16 | asyncpg + SQLAlchemy | 8 business tables, ACID persistence |
| **Data** | Redis 7 | Celery broker | Task queue (DB 1) + result backend (DB 2) |

## Key Design Decisions

1. **Async-first**: FastAPI + asyncpg + async Celery wrappers for non-blocking I/O
2. **Scraper isolation**: Each government source has its own scraper class (20+)
3. **LLM fallback chain**: Gemini → OpenAI → Mock (graceful degradation)
4. **Content dedup**: SHA-256 hashing prevents re-processing unchanged documents
5. **Rate limiting**: 50 LLM calls/hour enforced by Celery task rate limits
